        <h2 id="what-is">What is Majestic SEO?</h2>
        <p>Majestic is a specialised backlink analysis tool founded by Alex Chudnovsky in 2004 as Majestic-12 Ltd. It launched the original distributed web crawler on 1 Jan 2005, pivoted to commercial link intelligence in 2008, and rebranded from majesticseo.com to majestic.com in 2014. Headquartered in Birmingham, England (iCentrum, Holt Street, Birmingham B7 4BP).</p>

        <p>The company is <strong>independently owned and privately held</strong> — Majestic-12 Ltd never sold to a corporate. Unlike Moz (acquired by Ziff Davis) or Semrush (publicly traded), Majestic stayed bootstrapped via a unique Distributed Computing Partners model that turned early volunteer crawler contributors into shareholders.</p>

        <p>The product does five things:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Site Explorer</strong> — full backlink profile for any domain or URL</li>
          <li><strong>Trust Flow + Citation Flow</strong> — proprietary quality + quantity metrics</li>
          <li><strong>Historic Index</strong> — link data going back to 2006 (4.5T+ URLs)</li>
          <li><strong>Topical Trust Flow</strong> — categorises links by topic relevance</li>
          <li><strong>Bulk Analysis + Clique Hunter</strong> — cohort-style competitor link comparisons</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Majestic is <em>not</em>: a keyword tool, a content tool, a rank tracker, or a site auditor. It is a backlink microscope.</p>

        <h2 id="features">Majestic features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>

        <h3>1. Site Explorer + Fresh / Historic Index</h3>
        <p>Enter any URL or domain and Majestic returns the complete link profile. The Fresh Index tracks 227+ billion URLs with daily updates. The Historic Index spans 4.5+ trillion URLs dating to 2006 — the only place to find link data from a domain's earliest years. For domain investors and reputation forensics, this is the killer feature.</p>

        <h3>2. Trust Flow + Citation Flow</h3>
        <p>The pair of metrics that built Majestic's reputation. Citation Flow scores raw link quantity; Trust Flow scores quality by proximity to a curated seed set of trusted sites. The split helps identify spam: a high CF / low TF ratio is a classic red flag for PBNs and low-quality networks.</p>

        <h3>3. Topical Trust Flow</h3>
        <p>Every link is categorised by topic. You can see whether a backlink profile is dominated by, say, finance or gambling — useful both for verifying topical authority and for spotting unnatural patterns in competitor profiles.</p>

        <h3>4. Bulk Backlink Checker + Clique Hunter</h3>
        <p>Bulk Analysis lets you upload up to 1M URLs and get core metrics for each. Clique Hunter finds the domains linking to multiple competitors but not to you — the cleanest "link gap" view in any backlink tool.</p>

        <h3>5. API access</h3>
        <p>The API plan ($399.99/mo) exposes all link data programmatically. Used heavily by agencies running reporting at scale and by SaaS tools that need link data piped into their own dashboards.</p>

