        <h2 id="verdict">Is Majestic worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For link-building specialists and domain brokers: yes.</strong> Trust Flow is still the industry's most respected proprietary link metric, and the Historic Index is genuinely unique. If your job involves reputation forensics or historical link analysis, Majestic earns its $49–$100/mo.</p>

        <p><strong>For SEO suites that need backlink data: maybe.</strong> Ahrefs has fresher data and a better UI; Semrush has more tools around it. Majestic wins only if you specifically need pre-2013 link history or the Trust Flow score.</p>

        <p><strong>For business owners trying to grow traffic: no.</strong> Majestic does not write, optimise, publish, or rank-track anything. The real cost to actually use Majestic data productively lands at $2,500+/mo. A done-for-you platform ships faster and cheaper.</p>

